-- Colombian Stocks: Almacenes Exito Gains, Ecopetrol Declines
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2011-12-23T14:48:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-23/colombian-stocks-almacenes-exito-gains-ecopetrol-declines.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:36 a.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  gained 0.4 percent to 12,850.45, while the
Colcap Index rose 0.3 percent to 1,604.26.  Almacenes Exito SA (EXITO)  ,  Colombia ’s biggest publicly-
traded retailer, rose 1.8 percent to 26,000 pesos, a five-month
high. The company’s board of directors authorized its legal
representative to negotiate an agreement to purchase parent
company Casino Guichard-Perrachon SA’s minority stake of Exito-
controlled Disco and Devoto supermarkets in Uruguay, according
to a regulatory filing late yesterday.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
fell 0.1 percent to 4,295 pesos after the company said an oil
pipeline exploded in the central province of Risaralda as
thieves tried to steal gasoline. Ecopetrol said it suspended the
flow of oil through the pipeline at 3:49 a.m. local time and its
workers are in the area helping in the emergency.  At least seven people were killed and more than 60 injured
by the explosion, Caracol Radio reported, citing local
officials.  To contact the reporter on this story:
